<dt>Miscellaneous sites</dt>
</dl>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://canonizer.com/topic.asp/88" class="external text" title="http://canonizer.com/topic.asp/88" rel="nofollow">Canonizer.com open survey topic on theories of consciousness</a>. The more peoeple that participate the more comprehensive the survey. Expertise of participators is determined by a <a href="http://canonizer.com/topic.asp/81" class="external text" title="http://canonizer.com/topic.asp/81" rel="nofollow">Peer Ranking Process</a> that can be used to produce a quantitative measure of philosophic consensus for each theory.</li>
<li><a href="http://humwww.ucsc.edu/HistCon/" class="external text" title="http://humwww.ucsc.edu/HistCon/" rel="nofollow">History of Consciousness Graduate Program,</a> ("consciousness as forms of human expression and social action manifested in historical, cultural, and political contexts") at the University of California, Santa Cruz, headed by Dr. <a href="/wiki/Angela_Davis" title="Angela Davis">Angela Davis</a>* <a href="http://klab.caltech.edu/cns120/videos.php" class="external text" title="http://klab.caltech.edu/cns120/videos.php" rel="nofollow">Online lecture videos,</a> from an undergraduate course taught by <a href="/wiki/Christof_Koch" title="Christof Koch">Christof Koch</a> at <a href="/wiki/Caltech" title="Caltech" class="mw-redirect">Caltech</a> on the neurobiological basis of consciousness in 2004.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.scaruffi.com/mind.html" class="external text" title="http://www.scaruffi.com/mind.html" rel="nofollow">Piero Scaruffi's annotated bibliography on the mind</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.stanford.edu/group/maciverlab/" class="external text" title="http://www.stanford.edu/group/maciverlab/" rel="nofollow">Anesthesia and Drug effects on consciousness</a></li>
